-- Brazil Sets 125 Billion-Real 2011 Primary Surplus Target, Sen. Viana Says
-- Arnaldo Galvao
-- 2010-07-08T13:29:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/brazil-sets-125-billion-real-2011-primary-surplus-target-sen-viana-says.html

          
          
             Brazil set a primary surplus target,
or the surplus before interest payments, of 125 billion reais
for 2011, dropping the existing target as a ratio of gross
domestic product, Senator Tiao Viana, who oversaw the last
version of next yearâ€™s guidelines bill, told reporters in
Brasilia.  
 Brazil currently targets a primary surplus of 3.3 percent
of GDP.  
